# Circle (the HAL) is a git SUBMODULE -> our fork github.com/stephaneweg/circle,
# branch `onyx` (= upstream Step51 + our patches). It is therefore tracked, not
# ignored. After cloning Onyx:  git submodule update --init  (then build Circle).

# Build artifacts (transient outputs of the kernel/ and user/ builds).
*.o
*.a
*.d
*.img
*.elf
*.lst
*.map
*.bin
# Pi / WLAN firmware blobs elsewhere in the tree
*.dat
*.dtb

# Scratch / reference material (e.g. MenuetOS .asm sources kept for reference)
/temp/

# Editor / tooling
.claude/settings.local.json
.claude/settings.local.json.bak
# MS Office lock/temp files (e.g. ~$04-USER-GUIDE.docx while a doc is open)
~$*

# Generated by the kernel build (kapi_* symbol export)
user/kernel_syms.ld

# Python bytecode cache
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# ============================================================================
# Committed WHOLESALE -- these override the artifact globs above.
# ============================================================================

# The complete SD card image is committed (binaries included): the kernel .img, every
# app .elf, the NetSurf/GPL resources, skins, keymaps AND the Pi/WLAN firmware blobs, so
# the repo is a ready-to-flash card. NOTE: sdcard/etc/wpa_supplicant.conf stays tracked
# with its psk REDACTED by the tools/git-hooks/pre-commit hook (+ skip-worktree) -- the
# working copy keeps the real key for the card; the committed copy never does.
!/sdcard/
!/sdcard/**

# Vendored third-party dependencies (sources + prebuilt .a) so the build is self-contained:
# NetSurf + its library stack (libcss/libdom/libhubbub/...), mbedTLS, libwebp, libpng,
# libjpeg, zlib. The build points here by default (see user/netsurf/netsurf-app.mk etc.).
!/third_party/
!/third_party/**
# ...but NEVER the intermediate object files under third_party -- keep only the sources +
# the re-linkable .a libraries (see build-artifacts hygiene). Re-excluded after the negation.
# (Only *.o: patterns like *.d/*.map would wrongly catch source such as mbedtls/ChangeLog.d/
# or zlib's version-script zlib.map.)
third_party/**/*.o
# nsgenbind's host build output (the x86 binary + objects) -- artifact, not committed; its
# source IS vendored so it can be rebuilt (flex/bison) to regenerate the duktape bindings.
third_party/nsgenbind/build-*/
